{
  "texts": [
    "Unfortunately, we cannot directly access the function g since the two-step generation process is explicitly done by f LLM.",
    "However, obtaining C and S from the reverse direction is relatively more feasible.",
    "This involves employing a content extractor h -1 C and a style extractor h -1 S, which are respectively the inverse functions of h C and h S.",
    "Employing these content and style extractors allows us to disentangle the components of the model's response generation process, providing valuable insights into how framing bias is encoded through g.",
    "After obtaining the content and style variables, another challenge arises: how to analyze their biases."
  ]
}